1. ip addr – view your network interfaces and IP addresses.

2. ip route – see the routing table and default gateway.

3. ping 8.8.8.8 and ping google.com – test connectivity and verify DNS resolution.

4. nslookup google.com (or dig google.com) – query DNS records.

5. curl https://example.com – make an HTTP request and inspect the response.

6. ssh user@host – securely connect to another machine.

7. ss -tuln – list listening TCP and UDP ports.
